description: From Middle English misconstruen, equivalent to mis- +‎ construe.

verbs.description: misconstrue (third-person singular simple present misconstrues, present participle misconstruing, simple past and past participle misconstrued)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To interpret erroneously, to understand incorrectly; to misunderstand.
examples: […]  furthermore, I hope my meaning won’t be lost or misconstrued  […]
